BFN 

  [Text] Sulayman Franjiyah, minister of state for municipal 
and rural affairs, told AL-DIYAR that an agreement has been 
reached for him to assume the political supervision [al-ishraf 
al-siyasi] of the Lebanese Broadcasting Corporation [LBC]. 
Franjiyah denied that he has purchased shares in the 
corporation. 
  Minister Franjiyah expects that the law reorganizing audio 
and visual media will be issued within a period not exceeding 
one and a half months. 

